Now we start the Z part,

00:00:43.847 --> 00:00:46.430
which is a panel on Zika virus,

00:00:51.016 --> 00:00:55.036
and many or most of the
disabilities associated

00:00:55.036 --> 00:00:59.119
with Zika infection have
to do with disabilities.

00:01:00.086 --> 00:01:02.488
Since our planning and advisory committee,

00:01:02.488 --> 00:01:04.654
and thank you to all the planning

00:01:04.654 --> 00:01:08.732
and advisory committee
members who are here,

00:01:08.732 --> 00:01:12.501
recommended on behalf
of the regional centers

00:01:12.501 --> 00:01:16.813
and parents and families
that there's a lot of concern

00:01:16.813 --> 00:01:20.313
about Zika and its various considerations.

00:01:23.069 --> 00:01:25.464
So we have gotten together a panel

00:01:25.464 --> 00:01:28.464
of experts and we're starting where,

00:01:32.729 --> 00:01:36.062
I guess we should start with obstetrics.

00:01:37.871 --> 00:01:42.725
We are pleased to have our
first member of the panel,

00:01:42.725 --> 00:01:45.855
Dr. Kirsten Salmeen, who's
